{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SHpskzLw7Hg36W9K7cd7kH","type":"tool_result","content":"# GitHub Issue Summary: Implement todo-web Component\n\n**Title:** Implement component: todo-web #2\n\n**Task ID:** `05f15153-2326-48ad-b46c-bfab6d980f8b`\n\n## Core Requirements\n\nThis issue requests implementation of a React-based single-page application serving as the frontend for a todo management system. The application must be built with TypeScript, Vite, and Tailwind CSS, then deployed via Nginx on port 9090.\n\n## Key Responsibilities\n\nThe component should \"render a responsive single-page application with a category sidebar and task main panel, supporting full CRUD interactions\" while communicating exclusively with the todo-api backend through typed fetch wrappers. Client-side state management relies on React's built-in hooks (useState/useEffect).\n\n## Critical Features\n\n- **UI Components:** Sidebar with category list, main task panel with add-task form, task items with edit/delete actions\n- **Visual Indicators:** Red badges for overdue incomplete tasks, strikethrough styling for completed items\n- **API Integration:** Uses `VITE_API_BASE_URL` environment variable (baked in at Docker build time)\n- **Nginx Configuration:** Must include SPA fallback routing (`try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html`) and `/health` endpoint\n\n## Technical Constraints\n\nThe implementation cannot use runtime injection for the API base URL due to Vite's static build model. Timezone handling requires careful parsing (using local noon, not UTC midnight) to prevent off-by-one errors in overdue detection.\n\n## Deliverables Required\n\nComplete project structure with package.json, TypeScript config, Dockerfile (multi-stage build), nginx.conf, and a workload.yaml file for platform deployment."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0bcac202-cbc0-4f39-a1fe-0f8f308f7dc8","uuid":"713fe5bf-0776-452d-a447-001113a35c7f","timestamp":"2026-04-23T10:57:52.616Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":283015,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# GitHub Issue Summary: Implement todo-web Component\n\n**Title:** Implement component: todo-web #2\n\n**Task ID:** `05f15153-2326-48ad-b46c-bfab6d980f8b`\n\n## Core Requirements\n\nThis issue requests implementation of a React-based single-page application serving as the frontend for a todo management system. The application must be built with TypeScript, Vite, and Tailwind CSS, then deployed via Nginx on port 9090.\n\n## Key Responsibilities\n\nThe component should \"render a responsive single-page application with a category sidebar and task main panel, supporting full CRUD interactions\" while communicating exclusively with the todo-api backend through typed fetch wrappers. Client-side state management relies on React's built-in hooks (useState/useEffect).\n\n## Critical Features\n\n- **UI Components:** Sidebar with category list, main task panel with add-task form, task items with edit/delete actions\n- **Visual Indicators:** Red badges for overdue incomplete tasks, strikethrough styling for completed items\n- **API Integration:** Uses `VITE_API_BASE_URL` environment variable (baked in at Docker build time)\n- **Nginx Configuration:** Must include SPA fallback routing (`try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html`) and `/health` endpoint\n\n## Technical Constraints\n\nThe implementation cannot use runtime injection for the API base URL due to Vite's static build model. Timezone handling requires careful parsing (using local noon, not UTC midnight) to prevent off-by-one errors in overdue detection.\n\n## Deliverables Required\n\nComplete project structure with package.json, TypeScript config, Dockerfile (multi-stage build), nginx.conf, and a workload.yaml file for platform deployment.","durationMs":7406,"url":"https://github.com/asdlc-repos/kaj-test-15201/issues/2"}}
